race.description: Belle Of The Turf 28 Dec Class 1 Handicap
race.comment: CALL ME SASSY (4) bounced off her sound debut third, with a tenacious head victory over 1100m at Hawkesbury when a short-priced fav. Looks ready for this stiffer contest and rise in trip. OAKFIELD SATURN (2) progressive mare who was heavily supported on resumption when a fighting on-pace second to the handy Gunroom over 1250m at Newcastle. Won over this track and trip on debut and gets map favours. Goes close. MATCHSTICKS (6) has taken giant strides in her second preparation and was rewarded for her consistency when a slick on-pace winner over 1200m at Canberra. Gets a better set-up for this and is expected to go close. EAGLES BEWARE (3) frustrating in two runs back and has a host of gear changes for this. Shouldered the 60.5kg when fading badly in the straight to run fourth over 1150m at Beaumont (Newcastle). Goes into the place calculations.
